# Import libraries
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import statsmodels.api as sm
import yfinance as yf

# Download data from Yahoo Finance
df = yf.download('HG=F', start='2016-03-04', end='2023-12-19', interval='1d')

# Compute log returns
df['Returns'] = np.log(df['Close']) - np.log(df['Close'].shift(1))

# Compute lagged variables
df['Lag1'] = df['Returns'].shift(1)
df['Lag5'] = df['Returns'].shift(5)
df['Lag10'] = df['Returns'].shift(10)
df['Lag20'] = df['Returns'].shift(20)
df['Lag60'] = df['Returns'].shift(60)

# Drop missing values
df = df.dropna()

# Split data into train and test sets
train = df.loc['2016-03-04':'2020-12-31']
test = df.loc['2021-01-01':'2023-03-04']

# Define model
model = sm.tsa.SARIMAX(train['Returns'], order=(1,0,0), seasonal_order=(1,0,0,60))

# Fit model
results = model.fit()

# Print summary of results
print(results.summary())

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Plot copper prices
plt.plot(df.index, df['Close'], label='Copper prices')

# Plot seasonal lags
for lag in [5, 10, 20, 60]:
    plt.plot(df.index, df['Close'].shift(lag), label=f'Lag {lag}')

# Add legend and axis labels
plt.legend()
plt.xlabel('Date')
plt.ylabel('Copper Price')

# Show plot
plt.show()

import mplfinance as mpf

# Define plot style
style = mpf.make_mpf_style(base_mpf_style='charles', rc={'figure.figsize': (16, 8)})

# Prepare data for candlestick chart
ohlc = df[['Open', 'High', 'Low', 'Close']]

# Plot copper prices with seasonal lags
mpf.plot(ohlc, type='candle', style=style, figscale=2, ylabel='Copper Price', title='Copper Futures Price with Seasonal Lags',
         addplot=[mpf.make_addplot(df['Close'].shift(5), type='line', color='g', width=1, ylabel=''),
                  mpf.make_addplot(df['Close'].shift(10), type='line', color='b', width=1, ylabel=''),
                  mpf.make_addplot(df['Close'].shift(20), type='line', color='y', width=1, ylabel=''),
                  mpf.make_addplot(df['Close'].shift(60), type='line', color='r', width=1, ylabel=''),
                  mpf.make_addplot(df['Returns'], panel=1, ylabel='Returns', type='line', width=1)],
         panel_ratios=(0.75, 0.25))
